This article is a message from President Barack Obama to the Congress of the United States regarding the imposition of additional sanctions on Iran. The President explains that these sanctions are being implemented in response to the actions and policies of the Government of Iran, which threaten the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The President refers to previous executive orders and acts, such as the Comprehensive Iran Sanctions, Accountability, and Divestment Act of 2010, which have imposed trade and financial sanctions on Iran. The President states that these new sanctions will target individuals and entities that provide goods, services, technology, or support that contribute to Iran's development of petroleum resources or production of petrochemicals, which fund Iran's illicit nuclear activities. The article lists the criteria for the imposition of sanctions and the various forms of sanctions that may be imposed, including denial of export licenses, restrictions on financial transactions, and blocking of property. The President delegates the authority to the Secretary of the Treasury to take necessary actions to carry out the purposes of the order. The article concludes with the President urging all agencies of the United States Government to take appropriate measures to implement the sanctions.